## Formation

As stars more massive than 8 solar masses burn out their supply of hydrogen and create a helium core. This then fuses to Carbon, which fuses to Oxygen etc through Neon, Magnesium, Nickel, Sillicone, eventually to Iron, which does not fuse any more because that would require additional energy. TODO

